--->What is Concurrency
Concurrency means handling multiple tasks at the same time, but not necessarily executing them simultaneous
--->What is Parallel Programming?
Parallelism means executing multiple tasks literally at the same time.
--->Concurrency in Programming
Common Techniques:
Threads
Async / Await
Event loops
Example (Python - Concurrency)
import asyncio

async def task1():
    print("Task 1 started")
    await asyncio.sleep(2)
    print("Task 1 done")

async def task2():
    print("Task 2 started")
    await asyncio.sleep(1)
    print("Task 2 done")

async def main():
    await asyncio.gather(task1(), task2())

asyncio.run(main())

--->Tasks run concurrently (not truly parallel)

🔹 4. Parallel Programming in Python
Using multiprocessing:
from multiprocessing import Process

def task():
    print("Running in parallel")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    p1 = Process(target=task)
    p2 = Process(target=task)

    p1.start()
    p2.start()

    p1.join()
    p2.join()

Runs on multiple CPU cores
  
